div.p:
These veils are the deuce; they cover an enormous quantity of sins. Take my word
                  for it, when a woman decks herself with a light-blue veil, she is a loving one,
                  and likes life and fun.

"And even that I can change when necessary," he replied in a tone so different
                  from any she had ever heard from his lips, that she involuntarily looked around,
                  as though expecting to see a third person behind her.
